{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Browns Falls | photo = Browns Falls 2017.jpg | photo_width = 250px | photo_caption = Browns Falls 2017 Taken by Snapshotz Photography | map = Queensland | relief = yes | map_width = 250px | coordinates = {{coord|28|21|00|S|152|21|00|E|type:waterbody_region:AU-QLD_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref>{{Gazetteer of Australia|id=QLD4769|name=Browns Falls (QLD)}}</ref><ref>{{cite QPN|4769|Browns Falls|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref> | location = [[Killarney, Queensland|Killarney]], [[Southern Downs Region]], [[Queensland]], Australia | type = [[Waterfall#Types|Plunge]] | elevation = | height = {{convert|10|-|15|m}}<ref name=wow>{{cite web|url=http://www.world-of-waterfalls.com/australia-browns-falls.html|title=Browns Falls|work=World of Waterfalls|publisher=Johnny T. Cheng|date=9 May 2008|accessdate=18 May 2014}}</ref> | height_longest = | number_drops = | width = | average_width = | watercourse = Spring Creek | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Browns Falls''' is a [[Waterfall#Types|plunge waterfall]] on the [[Spring Creek (South Branch)]] in [[Killarney, Queensland|Killarney]], [[Southern Downs Region]], [[Queensland]], Australia.
==Location and features== The falls are located approximately {{convert|4.5|km}} east of [[Killarney, Queensland|Killarney]] in the [[Darling Downs]], just north of the Queensland/[[New South Wales]] border.<ref name=qdm10>{{cite map|publisher=[[RACQ]]|title=Gold Coast Northern Rivers|url= |edition=12|year=1998|cartography= |scale= |series=QDM10}}</ref> The falls descend approximately {{convert|10|-|15|m}} as it plunges over [[basalt]] columns into the valley floor.<ref name=wow/> Access to the falls is possible by walking approximately {{convert|600|m}} from the Browns Picnic Area.
Four other waterfalls are located in the area surrounding Killarney, including the [[Teviot Falls]] in the north at Teviot Gap, [[Queen Mary Falls]], [[Daggs Falls]] and [[Upper Browns Falls]].
