{{Other uses|Kaare Strøm (disambiguation){{!}}Kaare Strøm}}
'''Kaare Knutsson Münster Strøm''' (from 1949 only '''Kaare Strøm'''; 23 July 1902 &ndash; 28 February 1967) was a Norwegian [[limnology|limnologist]].
He was born in [[Nord-Aurdal]] as a son of pharmacist Knut Thorstensen Strøm (1863–1938) and his wife Marianne Münster (1870–1943). He was a grandson of [[Christian Münster]]. He grew up in [[Oslo|Kristiania]], [[examen artium|finished]] his secondary education at [[Frogner]] already in 1918, and began as a private student of [[Nordal Wille]]. He took the [[dr.philos.]] degree at the [[University of Oslo|Royal Frederick University]] in 1927 on the thesis ''Norwegian Mountain Algae''. He spent some time studying under [[August Thienemann]], and was a [[research fellow]] at the university from 1931 to 1936. He was promoted to [[docent]] in 1939 and professor in 1948. At first he was a professor in [[physical geography]] and [[limnology]], but from 1962 only in limnology. Strøm chaired the [[Norwegian Biological Society]] from 1934 to 1935, the [[Norwegian Geographical Association]] from 1944 to 1945 and the [[Norwegian Geographical Society]] from 1948 to 1949. He became a member of the [[Norwegian Academy of Science and Letters]] in 1943.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Kaare Strøm|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Dag|last=Klaveness|authorlink=Dag Klaveness (limnologist)|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Kaare_Str%C3%B8m/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=9 April 2010}}</ref>
Strøm was married to banker's daughter Agathe Hvistendahl from 1929 to 1949, and then to Kari Thorsen from December 1949. He died in February 1967 in [[Århus]], where he had a tenure as guest scholar.<ref name=nbl/>
