{{Infobox mountain | name = Pico Turquino | photo = PicoTurquino.jpg | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 1974 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 1974 | prominence_ref = | map = Cuba | map_caption = | map_size = 280 | label_position = left | label = Pico&nbsp;Turquino | listing = {{unbulleted list |[[List of the most isolated major summits of North America|North America isolated peaks]] 94th |[[List of Ultras of North America|Ultra prominent peak]] |[[List of countries by highest point|Country high point]] }} | translation = Turquino Peak | language = [[Spanish language|Spanish]] | location = [[Cuba]] | range = [[Sierra Maestra]] | coordinates = {{coord|19|59|22|N|76|50|09|W|type:mountain_region:CU_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | coordinates_ref = | topo = | type = | age = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }} '''Pico Turquino''' is the [[List of countries by highest point|highest point]] in [[Cuba]]. It is located in the southeast part of the island, in the [[Sierra Maestra]] [[mountain range]] in the municipality of [[Guamá, Cuba|Guamá]], [[Santiago de Cuba Province]].
==Overview== The name is believed to be a corruption of [[turquoise]] ({{lang-es|turquesa}}) peak, named so for the blue hues taken by the heights in certain views.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://emba.cubaminrex.cu/Default.aspx?tabid=8427|title=Pico Turquino, la montaña azul o el monte de los turcos|author=Cuban Foreign Ministry|accessdate=2007-10-18|language=Spanish|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111002065531/http://emba.cubaminrex.cu/Default.aspx?tabid=8427|archivedate=2011-10-02|df=}}</ref> It was first mentioned (under the name "Tarquino") on a map drawn by Gerardo Kramer in the late 18th century. It was first climbed in 1860 by F.W. Ramsden. [https://archive.org/stream/jstor-40590919/40590919_djvu.txt]
A bust of [[José Martí]], sculpted by [[Jilma Madera]], was placed on the peak to celebrate his centenary.
[[Turquino National Park]] is established on a {{convert|229.38|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}} area around the peak.<ref name=snap>{{cite web |url=http://www.snap.cu/listados.htm |title=Protected Areas |author=National Protected Areas System of Cuba |year=2005 |accessdate=2007-10-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070810220929/http://www.snap.cu/listados.htm |archivedate=2007-08-10 |df= }}</ref>
